      "role": "user",
      "content": "Oh, my bad. I thought you had the PDF uploaded to your system since you're the compliance AI. Let me just paste the text of Section 4.2 here for you then. \n\n[Section 4.2: Pricing Adjustments. Fuel rates are subject to market fluctuations. During peak demand months (November-January), the Supplier reserves the right to implement a price adjustment of up to 5% at their sole discretion, without prior written notice to SwiftRoute.]\n\nOkay, so reading that, does this contract give the supplier any unilateral rights to change the rates unexpectedly? I'm really looking for a clear 'yes' or 'no' so I can report back to the board about our risk.",
